<td width="120" align="center" valign="top" style="padding-left:10px;">
<div id="DiscussionTopicVote_3053">
<div id="IdeaScale_Vote" align="center"><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_3053', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2242&topicID=3053&vote=1')"><img alt="Vote Up" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_up.gif"/>&nbsp;Looks Promising!</a></div><div style="padding:5px;font-size:2em"><a onmouseout="setTimeout('Bubble.hide()', 500)" onmouseover="Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 7 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 4</div><div>Votes Against : 2</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_3053'))" style="text-decoration:none;" id="TopicVote_3053" href="javascript:Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 7 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 4</div><div>Votes Against : 2</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_3053'))">2</a></div><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_3053', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2242&topicID=3053&vote=-1')"><img alt="Vote Down" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_down.gif"/>&nbsp;I'm Not So Sure...</a></div></div>
</div>
</td>
<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_3053"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3053-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3053">Use Well-designed Feedback Systems instead of Central Control to Improve Web Design&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/4305-4049">Carie Fox and Philip Murphy </a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">7 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">An efficient and effective way to improve quality of websites without hampering creativity would be…   yup, transparency, specifically transparency about how well the website is working for the intended user.  There are plenty of examples in the private sector—was this answer useful?  How clear/interesting was this page?  How easy was it to find what you wanted?  The answers to these questions should be available in real time on every federal website.  The results of this query should be used in evaluating and rewarding not only the staff directly responsible for the site but also the manager for that unit.  <br/><br/>In an emerging field, this is a better way to identify and reach excellence than trying to set and enforce national rules.<br/><br/>(See also the usage statistics recommendations—excellent!)<br/></div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_3053" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_3053', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2242&topicID=3053')">Comments (1)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_3053"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2242">New Strategies and Techniques</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=foxand murphy">foxand murphy</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_3053"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr id="row_3052">
<td width="120" align="center" valign="top" style="padding-left:10px;">
<div id="DiscussionTopicVote_3052">
<div id="IdeaScale_Vote" align="center"><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_3052', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2242&topicID=3052&vote=1')"><img alt="Vote Up" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_up.gif"/>&nbsp;Looks Promising!</a></div><div style="padding:5px;font-size:2em"><a onmouseout="setTimeout('Bubble.hide()', 500)" onmouseover="Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 7 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 7</div><div>Votes Against : 4</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_3052'))" style="text-decoration:none;" id="TopicVote_3052" href="javascript:Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 7 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 7</div><div>Votes Against : 4</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_3052'))">3</a></div><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_3052', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2242&topicID=3052&vote=-1')"><img alt="Vote Down" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_down.gif"/>&nbsp;I'm Not So Sure...</a></div></div>
</div>
</td>
<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_3052"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3052-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3052">Planning and Collaboration Operate from the Same Platform&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/4305-4049">Carie Fox and Philip Murphy </a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">7 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Technology gives the public the ability to comment from the same platform as the planners, thus greatly increasing the likelihood that the comments themselves will be salient, that the planners will be able to act on the comments, and that the system (decision-maker and agency) will have a positive reinforcing loop.  For instance, if planners are using GIS, then commenters should be able to use GIS in similar ways.  Instead of agencies using a tacit (and invisible) decision framework and asking the commenter to guess at the underlying logic of a decision—and planners to guess at the commenters’ guesses—make the decision framework explicit and give the commenters access to that.<br/><br/>When the agency designs their decision-making process, make it conducive to collaboration* by building outreach and planning upon the same foundation rather than treating outreach as an add-on.<br/><br/>*If collaboration is a goal<br/></div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_3052" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_3052', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2242&topicID=3052')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_3052"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2242">New Strategies and Techniques</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=foxandmurphy">foxandmurphy</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_3052"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr id="row_3051">
<td width="120" align="center" valign="top" style="padding-left:10px;">
<div id="DiscussionTopicVote_3051">
<div id="IdeaScale_Vote" align="center"><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_3051', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2242&topicID=3051&vote=1')"><img alt="Vote Up" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_up.gif"/>&nbsp;Looks Promising!</a></div><div style="padding:5px;font-size:2em"><a onmouseout="setTimeout('Bubble.hide()', 500)" onmouseover="Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 7 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 5</div><div>Votes Against : 3</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_3051'))" style="text-decoration:none;" id="TopicVote_3051" href="javascript:Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 7 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 5</div><div>Votes Against : 3</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_3051'))">2</a></div><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_3051', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2242&topicID=3051&vote=-1')"><img alt="Vote Down" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_down.gif"/>&nbsp;I'm Not So Sure...</a></div></div>
</div>
</td>
<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_3051"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3051-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3051">Design Planning and Decision-Making Processes with “Outreachability” in Mind&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/4305-4049">Carie Fox and Philip Murphy </a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">7 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">When designing planning and decision-making processes, one of the criteria should be “does this support the level of collaboration to which we aspire?”  If differing planning or modeling approaches score similarly for cost effectiveness, relevance, and planner or scientific acceptance, then the approach that lends itself more readily to wider collaboration (and if wider collaboration is a goal), then that approach should be chosen.  Likewise, once a planning or scientific approach is chosen, thinking early about each step “how will this support various levels of participation?” will provide for a much stronger synergy between good science, good planning, and good collaboration.<br/></div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_3051" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_3051', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2242&topicID=3051')">Comments (1)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_3051"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2242">New Strategies and Techniques</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=foxandmurphy">foxandmurphy</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_3051"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
</table>

